The paper deals with algorithmic game theory and mechanism design, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and submodular functions, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
